Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter South African factory output contracted for a fifteenth month in August even as coronavirus-lockdown measures were eased allowing activity to resume in the sector. Output fell 10.8%, compared with a revised 10.2% decline in July, Statistics South Africa said Monday in a report published on its website. The median estimate of seven economists in a Bloomberg survey was for a 7.8% drop. Production rose 3.6% in the month.